                              <p>
                                <p style="font-size: 19px; color: black; text-align: center;">
                                    <i>“Do not spoil what you have by desiring what you have not; remember that what you now have was once among the things you only hoped for.”<br>
                                        ~Epicurus 
     
                                     </i>
                                   </p>
                              </p>
                              <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                Capitalism and constant competition has engulfed our lives in more ways than we can imagine. In this fast-paced and constantly changing modern world, we are constantly seeking something more, something better. Big dreams, inspiring ambitions and great destinations cloud our minds. There is nothing wrong with hoping for a better future. But you know it’s time to pause and reflect when you start living for the future and forget to enjoy the present. Contentment is a gift that you can cultivate to be at peace with what you have. Here are a few things that you can do to be content with your life and find happiness in the little things:

                                </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';"><li>●	Gain a Realistic Perspective on Self-Love </li>
                                  <li>●	Reflect on Your Progress</li>
                                  <li>●	Keep a Gratitude Box</li>
                                  <li>●	Differentiate between Ambition and Greed </li>
                                  <li>●	Don’t Compare Yourself to Others </li>
                                  <li>●	Rejoice in the Little Things /li>
                                  <li>●	Count Your Blessings </li>
                                  <li>●	Remind Yourself of the Struggles of Others </li>
                                  <li>● Don’t Postpone Happiness  </li>
                                  <li>●	Live in the Present </li>
                              
                                  
                                  
                                  	</ul> 
                                  
                              </p>
                              <div class="row" >
                                <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                    <img alt="Girl and boy celebrating together" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/How%20to%20Be%20Content%20with%20What%20You%20Have%3F%2F10820.jpg?alt=media&token=60506043-b88f-4d4f-9fa8-7c902650a9d7" >
